    • Field Detail

      • AVALON_FP_LOCK

        public static final java.lang.Object AVALON_FP_LOCK
        This lock prevents two calls at the same time into the Avalon Fingerprint functionality, which has caused crashes under Windows 7 before. Once there is a fix implemented in the RDKit (or somewhere else?) we can remove this lock again.

      • getSpecification

        public FingerprintSettings getSpecification(int iTorsionPathLength,
                                            int iMinPath,
                                            int iMaxPath,
                                            int iAtomPairMinPath,
                                            int iAtomPairMaxPath,
                                            int iNumBits,
                                            int iRadius,
                                            int iLayerFlags,
                                            boolean bIsRooted,
                                            java.lang.String strAtomListColumn,
                                            boolean bTreatAtomListAsIncludeList)
        Creates a new fingerprint settings object for a fingerprint type. Not all parameters are used for all fingerprints. This method takes are that only those parameters are included in the fingerprint specification, if they are are really used.
        Parameters:
        iTorsionPathLength - Torsion Path Length value. Can be -1 (#UNAVAILABLE.
        iMinPath - Min Path value. Can be -1 (#UNAVAILABLE.
        iMaxPath - Min Path value. Can be -1 (#UNAVAILABLE.
        iAtomPairMinPath - Min Path value. Can be -1 (#UNAVAILABLE.
        iAtomPairMaxPath - Min Path value. Can be -1 (#UNAVAILABLE.
        iNumBits - Num Bits (Length) value. Can be -1 (#UNAVAILABLE.
        iRadius - Radius value. Can be -1 (#UNAVAILABLE.
        iLayerFlags - Layer Flags value. Can be -1 (#UNAVAILABLE.
        bIsRooted - Flag to set if a rooted fingerprint is desired.
        strAtomListColumnName - Atom list column name for rooted fingerprints.
        bTreatAtomListAsIncludeList - Flag to tell if atom list atoms shall be included (true) or excluded (false).
        Returns:
        Specification of the fingerprint based on the passed in values. Never null.

      • validateSpecification

        public void validateSpecification(FingerprintSettings settings,
                                  DataTableSpec tableSpec)
                           throws InvalidSettingsException
        Validates the passed in settings for a fingerprint type. This basis method checks two things: 1. That the setting object is not null, 2. If the fingerprint type can calculate rooted fingerprints and a rooted fingerprint is desired, it checks that the atom list column name is set and if a table specification is provided it checks if that column exists. 3. If a count-based fingerprint is desired it checks if the fingerprint type supports this.
        Parameters:
        settings - Fingerprint settings to be validated.
        tableSpec - Table specification that will be used to validate rooted fingerprint settings. This method will look if a rooted fingerprint is desired that the specified atom list column is contained in the specified table specification (if set) and if the data type is correct.
        Throws:
        InvalidSettingsException - Thrown, if settings are invalid and cannot be used.

      • calculate

        public ExplicitBitVect calculate(ROMol mol,
                                 FingerprintSettings settings)
        Calculates the bit based fingerprint based on the specified settings. Important: It is the responsibility of the caller of the function to free memory for the returned fingerprint when it is not needed anymore. Call the ExplicitBitVect#delete() for this purpose.
        Parameters:
        mol - Molecule to calculate fingerprint for. Must not be null.
        Fingerprint - settings. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        Fingerprint or null.
        Throws:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - Thrown, if fingerprint type does not support calculation of bit-based fingerprints.

      • calculateRooted

        public ExplicitBitVect calculateRooted(ROMol mol,
                                       UInt_Vect atomList,
                                       FingerprintSettings settings)
        Calculates the bit-based rooted fingerprint based on the specified settings. Important: It is the responsibility of the caller of the function to free memory for the returned fingerprint when it is not needed anymore. Call the ExplicitBitVect#delete() for this purpose.
        Parameters:
        mol - Molecule to calculate fingerprint for. Must not be null.
        atomList - Include or exclude list of atoms (depends on settings). Can be null.
        Fingerprint - settings. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        Fingerprint or null.
        Throws:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - Thrown, if fingerprint type does not support calculation of rooted bit-based fingerprints.

      • parseString

        public static FingerprintType parseString(java.lang.String str)
        Tries to determine the fingerprint type based on the passed in string. First it will try to determine it by assuming that the passed in string is the name of the fingerprint type (Enum.name(). If this fails, it will compare the string representation trying to find a match there (toString(). If none is found it will return null.

      • isCompatible

        public static boolean isCompatible(FingerprintSettings fps1,
                                   FingerprintSettings fps2)
        Determines, if the two specified fingerprint setting objects are compatible. They are compatible if they are both not null and if the settings are the same except for the detail information for rooted fingerprints (atom list column).
        Parameters:
        fps1 - Fingerprint settings 1. Can be null.
        fps2 - Fingerprint settings 2. Can be null.
        Returns:
        True, if both settings are compatible. False otherwise.
